major%20cosmic%20event%20on%20Friday%20as%20NASA%20said%20that%20two%20aeroplane-sized%20asteroids%20--%202024%20XW15%20and%202024%20XC16%20--%20are%20all%20set%20to%20fly%20past%20Earth.%20Although%20the%20distances%20of%20the%20two%20asteroids%20were%20called%20%26quot%3Bnear%20misses%2C%26quot%3B%20scientists%20at%20the%20US%20Space%20Agency%20said%20there%20was%20no%20risk%20to%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsteroid%202024%20XW15%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeasuring%20210%20feet%2C%20the%20asteroid%202024%20XW15%20is%20said%20to%20be%20similar%20to%20a%20large%20aeroplane.%20It%20was%20expected%20to%20approach%20the%20planet%20on%20Friday%20at%209%3A42%20AM%20IST%2C%20travelling%20at%20a%20massive%20speed%20of%2025%2C859%20miles%20per%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20to%20pass%20within%204%2C010%2C000%20miles%20of%20the%20Earth%2C%20around%2016%20times%20the%20distance%20between%20the%20planet%20and%20the%20Moon.%20Experts%20said%20there%20was%20nothing%20to%20worry%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsteroid%202024%20XC16%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20asteroid%20confirmed%20to%20fly%20past%20the%20Earth%20is%202024%20XC16%2C%20which%20measures%20roughly%20100%20feet%20in%20diameter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20expected%20to%20move%20past%20the%20planet%20at%20the%20speed%20of%2046%2C269%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20while%20its%20closest%20approach%20will%20be%20within%203%2C280%2C000%20miles%20of%20the%20planet.%20While%20this%20distance%20is%20less%20compared%20with%20the%20asteroid%202024%20XW15%2C%20it%20is%20considered%20far%20enough%20to%20ensure%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsteroids%2C%20like%20the%202024%20XW15%2C%20are%20relics%20of%20the%20early%20solar%20system%20that%20dates%20back%20to%204.6%20billion%20years.%20These%20space%20rocks%20help%20researchers%20and%20scientists%20understand%20the%20Earth's%20history%20and%20the%20cosmos.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20risk%20posed%20by%20these%20asteroids%20is%20not%20hypothetical.%20There%20have%20been%20instances%20when%20their%20collision%20has%20led%20to%20devastating%20consequences.%20Among%20the%20highly%20popular%20examples%20is%20the%20asteroid%20which%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20wiped%20out%20the%20dinosaurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20major%20events%20underscore%20the%20need%20to%20monitor%20these%20space%20rocks%20and%20keep%20track%20of%20their%20movements%20to%20understand%20their%20trajectories.%20Advanced%20monitoring%20plays%20a%20valuable%20role%20in%20the%20timely%20implementation%20of%20mitigation%20strategies%2C%20should%20any%20of%20these%20asteroids%20pose%20a%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETracking%20the%20orbits%20of%20these%20asteroids%20gives%20critical%20data%20for%20planetary%20defence%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20NASA%20has%20developed%20advanced%20tools%20to%20track%20near-Earth%20objects%20(NEOs).%20NASA-backed%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20has%20employed%20cutting-edge%20radar%20systems%20to%20analyse%20the%20path%20of%20asteroids.%20Missions%20such%20as%20OSIRIS-REx%20and%20Hayabusa2%20have%20been%20highly%20successful%20in%20bringing%20asteroid%20samples%20back%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734066900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2F7hfg98pg_asteroid-generic-_625x300_04_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-says-two-airplane-sized-asteroids-flying-past-earth-at-alarming-speed-today-7237415%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Space%20enthusiasts%20are%20in%20for%20a%20major%20cosmic%20event%20on%20Friday%20as%20NASA%20said%20that%20two%20aeroplane-sized%20asteroids%20--%202024%20XW15%20and%202024%20XC16%20--%20are%20all%20set%20to%20fly%20past%20Earth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-says-two-airplane-sized-asteroids-flying-past-earth-at-alarming-sp