%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20products%20and%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smart%20decisions%20with%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222769%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Peter%20Rothbart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6227c60fdcce010019a748be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221384%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Rothbart%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20learning%20how%20to%20budget%2C%20I%20meticulously%20tracked%20every%20penny%20in%20a%20spreadsheet.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20don't%20do%20it%20anymore%20because%20I%20learned%20my%20own%20habits%20over%20time%2C%20and%20tracking%20became%20a%20stressful%20waste.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENow%20I%20use%20the%20bucketing%20method%2C%20which%20works%20but%20lets%20me%20focus%20on%20things%20other%20than%20every%20penny%20I%20have.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20began%20saving%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%5C%22%3Einvesting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20sought%20a%20lot%20of%20advice%20from%20personal%20finance%20gurus%20like%20Suze%20Orman%20and%20J.D.%20Roth.%20I%20wanted%20to%20both%20preserve%20what%20limited%20financial%20resources%20I%20had%20at%20my%20disposal%20and%20make%20my%20future%20earnings%20grow.%20These%20gurus%20taught%20me%20that%20developing%20sound%20money%20habits%20was%20a%20vital%20first%20step%20to%20achieving%20both%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20they%20sometimes%20disagreed%20about%20what%20those%20sound%20money%20habits%20should%20be%2C%20one%20recurring%20suggestion%20I%20encountered%20was%20to%20track%20every%20last%20penny%20I%20spent%20or%20earned.%20The%20premise%20was%20that%20before%20deciding%20where%20my%20money%20%3Cem%3Eshould%3C%2Fem%3E%20go%2C%20I%20needed%20a%20clear%20picture%20of%20where%20it%20was%20already%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20tracked%20literally%20every%20penny%20coming%20in%20or%20out%20of%20my%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20by%20first%20tracking%20my%20expenses%20in%20a%20simple%20Excel%20spreadsheet.%20I%20diligently%20logged%20every%20last%20cent%20that%20came%20in%20or%20out%20of%20my%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20included%20big%20things%20like%20paychecks%20and%20bills%20%E2%80%94%20but%20sometimes%20I'd%20log%20even%20just%20a%20quarter%20paid%20to%20a%20parking%20meter%2C%20or%20a%20quarter%20found%20on%20the%20street.%20I%20noted%20the%20date%2C%20location%2C%20payment%20method%2C%20and%20amount%2C%20along%20with%20a%20brief%20description%20for%20each%20entry.%20I%20used%20color%20coding%20to%20help%20me%20categorize%20and%20evaluate%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20chronicling%20my%20finances%20in%20such%20fine%20detail%20was%20very%20tedious%2C%20knowing%20how%20much%20I%20really%20spent%20from%20month%20to%20month%20helped%20a%20lot%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fhow-to-budget%5C%22%3Esetting%20a%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20like%20rent%20and%20health%20insurance%20premiums%20were%20easy%20to%20plan%20for%2C%20but%20my%20spreadsheet%20also%20clarified%20exactly%20how%20much%20I%20was%20dropping%20on%20%26quot%3Bnon-essentials%26quot%3B%20like%20desserts%2C%20movie%20rentals%2C%20and%20dodgeball%20league%20fees.%20Documenting%20these%20miscellaneous%20expenses%20enabled%20me%20to%20budget%20for%20my%20full%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fcost-of-living-comparison-buy-rent%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20living%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20what%20most%20readily%20came%20to%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20confronting%20my%20spending%20habits%20in%20black%20and%20white%20gave%20me%20an%20honest%20view%20of%20where%20my%20money%20was%20going.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20in%20the%20spreadsheet%20were%20objective.%20I%20couldn't%20downplay%20them%20or%20trick%20myself%20into%20believing%20I%20spent%20more%20or%20less%20than%20I%20really%20did.%20Knowledge%20is%20power%2C%20and%20knowing%20how%20I%20really%20spent%20my%20money%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20how%20I%20liked%20to%20think%20I%20spent%20it%20%E2%80%94%20was%20empowering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20spreadsheet%20illuminated%20areas%20where%20I%20was%20overspending%2C%20or%20even%20underspending.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20my%20trial%20period%20expired%20at%20the%20gym%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20wasn't%20getting%20my%20money's%20worth%20paying%20the%20full%20rate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20was%20using%20less%20than%20a%20third%20of%20what%20I'd%20budgeted%20for%20clothing%20and%20car%20repairs.%20Identifying%20these%20imbalances%20helped%20me%20recognize%20when%20I%20was%20being%20extravagant%20or%20tightfisted%2C%20and%20to%20reallocate%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20spreadsheet%20stopped%20being%20useful%20and%20became%20exhausting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tracked%20my%20purchases%20this%20way%20for%20several%20years%2C%20but%20once%20I%20got%20a%20bead%20on%20my%20spending%20habits%20and%20devised%20a%20suitable%20budget%2C%20continuing%20to%20record%20every%20transaction%20didn't%20seem%20useful%20anymore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20already%20knew%20how%20much%20I%20typically%20spent%20on%20staples%20like%20groceries%20and%20gas%2C%20and%20I%20had%20wrangled%20my%20other%20assorted%20expenses%20to%20the%20point%20that%20they%20no%20longer%20needed%20regular%20attention.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20my%20income%20rose%2C%20my%20spending%20remained%20nearly%20static%20as%20my%20extra%20earnings%20went%20mostly%20into%20savings.%20Adding%20more%20data%20points%20to%20the%20spreadsheet%20didn't%20give%20me%20new%20information%2C%20it%20simply%20rehashed%20the%20information%20I%20already%20had%20for%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20I%20considered%20that%20staying%20vigilant%20would%20help%20me%20detect%20future%20changes%20in%20my%20consumption.%20That%20feedback%20could%20keep%20me%20from%20sliding%20back%20into%20old%20spending%20habits%20or%20serve%20as%20an%20early%20warning%20system%20for%20other%20concerns%2C%20like%20higher%20fuel%20costs%20that%20hint%20at%20car%20troubles%2C%20for%20example.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20overspending%20had%20never%20been%20a%20problem%20for%20me%2C%20I%20was%20confident%20I%20wouldn't%20start%20leaking%20money%20if%20I%20took%20my%20eye%20off%20the%20ball.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20considered%20tweaking%20my%20approach%20so%20it%20would%20demand%20less%20persistent%20effort%2C%20perhaps%20by%20no%20longer%20tracking%20purchases%20below%20a%20minimum%20threshold%2C%20or%20by%20seeking%20technological%20solutions%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudgeting%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20automate%20the%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20was%20another%2C%20more%20pressing%20reason%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20keep%20tracking%20every%20penny%3A%20Being%20hyper-aware%20of%20my%20spending%20gave%20me%20needless%20guilt%20over%20purchases%20that%20weren't%20strictly%20essential%2C%20even%20if%20I%20had%20budgeted%20for%20them%20properly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20end%20up%20feeling%20bad%20about%20buying%20things%20that%20were%20supposed%20to%20make%20me%20feel%20good%2C%20because%20minding%20every%20last%20cent%20had%20trained%20me%20to%20think%20that%20every%20last%20cent%20was%20crucial%20to%20my%20financial%20well-being.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20system%20was%20no%20longer%20working%20for%20me%2C%20so%20it%20was%20time%20to%20look%20for%20another.%20I%20still%20needed%20to%20pay%20%3Cem%3Esome%3C%2Fem%3E%20attention%20to%20where%20my%20money%20went%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20shift%20from%20scrutinizing%20my%20finances%20constantly%20in%20micro-detail%20to%20looking%20only%20periodically%20at%20the%20bigger%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20switched%20to%20bucketing%2C%20which%20makes%20budgeting%20now%20much%20easier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20a%20solution%20when%20I%20began%20using%20a%20strategy%20known%20as%20'bucketing%2C'%20which%20involves%20separating%20funds%20that%20are%20earmarked%20for%20different%20purposes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20seeded%20my%20primary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-checking-accounts%5C%22%3Echecking%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20enough%20to%20cover%20roughly%20two%20months%20of%20living%20costs%2C%20and%20I%20put%20funds%20reserved%20for%20savings%2C%20business%20expenses%2C%20taxes%2C%20and%20non-essentials%20into%20their%20own%20segregated%20sub-accounts.%20I%20then%20budgeted%20for%20monthly%20contributions%20to%20each%20sub-account%2C%20ensuring%20that%20all%20those%20bases%20would%20be%20covered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20strategy%20vastly%20simplified%20the%20task%20of%20tracking%20my%20finances.%20So%20long%20as%20it%20stayed%20close%20to%20the%20amount%20I%20seeded%20initially%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20wasn't%20overspending.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20balance%20of%20my%20main%20checking%20account%20was%20significantly%20higher%20or%20lower%20than%20expected%2C%20I%20could%20go%20back%20through%20my%20invoices%2C%20checkbook%2C%20and%20credit%20card%20statements%20to%20figure%20out%20why.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20foolproof%20approach%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20met%20my%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20developing%20sound%20money%20habits%20is%20important%2C%20recognizing%20when%20they've%20outlived%20their%20usefulness%20is%20also%20important.%20I'm%20grateful%20for%20the%20advice%20I%20recei