lping%20100%2B%20Local%20Farmers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMotivated%20by%20the%20emerging%20market%20for%20dehydrated%20flowers%2C%20Shivraj%20Nishad%20from%20Kanpur%E2%80%99s%20Shekhpur%20village%20embarked%20on%20a%20remarkable%20journey%20in%202019%20that%20would%20alter%20his%20life%20and%20uplift%20the%20lives%20of%20many%20in%20his%20community.%20Leaving%20his%20job%20as%20a%20pharma%20executive%2C%20the%2032-year-old%20post-grad%20from%20Lucknow%E2%80%99s%20Dr%20A%20P%20J%20Abdul%20Kalam%20Technical%20University%20initiated%20a%20small-scale%20venture%20focused%20on%20cultivating%2C%20harvesting%2C%20and%20dehydrating%20local%20flowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20earning%20only%20Rs%2021%2C000%2C%20and%20the%20job%20involved%20frequent%20travel%2C%20keeping%20me%20away%20from%20home%20for%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Nishad.%20%E2%80%9CI%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20farming%2C%20but%20rather%20than%20continue%20with%20traditional%20crops%20on%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20half-acre%20plot%2C%20I%20chose%20to%20grow%20butterfly%20pea%2C%20which%20thrives%20well%20here.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F347227%2Ffarmer-lemon-man-of-raebareli-uttar-pradesh-anand-mishra-earning-five-times-more-in-lakhs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReturns%20from%20growing%20traditional%20crops%20were%20minimal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20input%20costs%20were%20high.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20traditional%20crops%20to%20dehydrated%20flowers%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENishad%20began%20his%20venture%20with%20just%2010%20kg%20of%20dehydrated%20flowers%20and%20now%20sells%20between%2020%20and%2030%20tonnes%20annually%2C%20mostly%20sourced%20from%20Shekhpur%20and%20neighbouring%20villages.%20These%20villagers%20were%20traditionally%20growing%20crops%20like%20paddy%2C%20wheat%2C%20and%20lentils.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20the%20sale%20of%20fresh%20flowers%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20lucrative%20enough%3B%20if%20they%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20sell%20them%2C%20the%20flowers%20would%20either%20be%20brought%20back%20home%20or%20discarded%20into%20the%20river.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F328701%2Fpunjab-farmer-starts-floriculture-exotic-flowers-help-earn-more-profits%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENishad%20convinced%20the%20farmers%20to%20grow%20these%20flowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20sell%20them%20to%20him.%20With%20his%20encouragement%2C%20the%20villagers%20took%20floriculture%20more%20seriously%20and%20now%20grow%20seven%20different%20varieties%20%E2%80%94%20Nishad%20purchases%20their%20entire%20harvest.%20The%20growers%20are%20paid%20promptly%20and%20no%20longer%20have%20to%20travel%2015%20km%20to%20the%20nearest%20%3Cem%3Emandi%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewith%20their%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22When%20Nishad%20switched%20to%20farming%2C%20he%20chose%20to%20grow%20butterfly%20pea%20flowers%20instead%20of%20traditional%20crops.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-388809%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWhen%20Nishad%20switched%20to%20farming%2C%20he%20chose%20to%20grow%20butterfly%20pea%20flowers%20instead%20of%20traditional%20crops.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Nishad%20started%20with%20butterfly%20peas%20and%20has%20since%20expanded%20his%20product%20line%20to%20include%20rose%2C%20hibiscus%2C%20marigold%2C%20calendula%2C%20lemongrass%2C%20spearmint%2C%20tulsi%2C%20jasmine%2C%20chamomile%2C%20and%20ginger%20%E2%80%94%20all%20used%20for%20making%20teas%2C%20syrups%2C%20or%20preserves.%20%E2%80%9CI%20earn%20around%20a%20lakh%20rupees%20a%20month%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Nishad%2C%20with%20a%20turnover%20ranging%20between%2020%20to%2030%20tonnes%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20established%20a%20small%20centre%20outside%20the%20village%20where%20farmers%20from%20the%20nearby%20area%20come%20to%20sell%20their%20harvested%20flowers%20twice%20a%20day%20%E2%80%94%20once%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20once%20in%20the%20evening.%20These%20fresh%20flowers%20are%20dehydrated%20within%2012%20to%2015%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20solar%20dryers%20was%20a%20key%20turning%20point%20in%20Nishad%E2%80%99s%20business%20venture.%20Initially%2C%20he%20dried%20flowers%20in%20an%20open%20environment%2C%20exposed%20to%20dust%2C%20bird%20droppings%2C%20and%20unpredictable%20weather%20conditions%2C%20which%20could%20damage%20the%20product.%20Eventually%2C%20he%20invested%20in%20a%20solar%20dryer%20costing%20Rs%2060%2C000%2C%20which%20not%20only%20accelerated%20the%20dehydration%20process%20but%20also%20ensured%20that%20the%20product%20remained%20pure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESolar%20dryers%3A%20A%20game-changer%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20solar%20dryer%2C%20consisting%20of%20trays%20placed%20on%20a%20metal%20stand%20under%20a%20roof%20of%20polycarbonate%20sheets%20with%20a%20total%20area%20of%20about%20five%20square%20