ern%20bank%20of%20the%20Brahmaputra%20River%20in%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20Darrang%20and%20Sonitpur%20districts%2C%20Orang%20National%20Park%20is%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98Mini%20Kaziranga%E2%80%99%3B%20like%20Kaziranga%20National%20Park%2C%20it%20is%20home%20to%20a%20significant%20population%20of%20the%20endangered%20one-horned%20rhinoceros%20and%20shares%20a%20similar%20landscape.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECovering%20only%2079.28%20square%20kilometres%2C%20the%20Orang%20National%20Park%20is%20a%20vital%20hotspot%20for%20wildlife%2C%20home%20to%20iconic%20species%20like%20the%20magnificent%20endangered%20one-horned%20rhinoceros%2C%20Bengal%20tiger%2C%20and%20pygmy%20hog.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20historical%20overview%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOriginally%20inhabited%20by%20local%20tribes%2C%20the%20area%20that%20is%20now%20Orang%20National%20Park%20was%20abandoned%20by%20its%20tribal%20population%20in%20the%20early%201900s%20due%20to%20an%20epidemic.%20In%201915%2C%20the%20British%20colonial%20authorities%20designated%20it%20as%20a%20game%20reserve%2C%20an%20area%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F383592%2Fwildlife-conservation-sharvan-patel-rajasthan-whatsapp-group-save-species-habitats%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewildlife%20conservation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20controlled%20hunting%2C%20and%20over%20the%20years%2C%20it%20evolved%20into%20the%20wildlife%20sanctuary%20it%20is%20today.%20In%201999%2C%20it%20officially%20became%20Orang%20National%20Park%20%E2%80%94%20a%20protected%20area%20with%20a%20rich%20history%20and%20even%20richer%20biodiversity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20park%20is%20located%20in%20an%20alluvial%20floodplain%2C%20formed%20by%20the%20coming%20together%20of%20several%20rivers%2C%20including%20the%20Pachnoi%2C%20Belsiri%2C%20and%20Dhansiri%2C%20which%20join%20the%20Brahmaputra.%20This%20geography%20makes%20the%20park%20especially%20vulnerable%20to%20seasonal%20flooding%2C%20but%20also%20supports%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20plant%20and%20animal%20life%2C%20including%2012%20natural%20wetlands%20and%2026%20artificial%20water%20bodies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20wildlife%20of%20Orang%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Orang%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20strengths%20is%20its%20impressive%20array%20of%20wildlife.%20The%20park%20is%20most%20famous%20for%20being%20the%20northernmost%20stronghold%20of%20the%20great%20Indian%20one-horned%20rhinoceros.%20As%20per%202022%20numbers%2C%20it%20is%20home%20to%20around%20125%20rhinos%2C%20the%20numbers%20for%20which%20have%20been%20steadily%20increasing.%20The%20park%20also%20houses%20a%20variety%20of%20other%20large%20mammals%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F360895%2Fvivek-menon-wildlife-trust-of-india-wildlife-conservation-anti-poaching-elephant-corridors%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Asiatic%20elephant%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20wild%20water%20buffalo%2C%20and%20the%20hog%20deer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20750px)%20100vw%2C%20750px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcudie-1732858636.webp%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20pygmy%20hog%20in%20Assam's%20Orang%20National%20Park%2C%20standing%2025-30%20cm%20tall.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcudie-1732858636.webp%20750w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcudie-1732858636-300x240.webp%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcudie-1732858636-500x400.webp%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fcudie-1732858636-150x120.webp%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-384