ourhood.%20These%20experiences%20left%20a%20lasting%20impact%2C%20and%20it%20was%20during%20this%20time%20that%20she%20began%20to%20fully%20understand%20the%20marginalisation%20her%20community%20faced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-500x500.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20image%20of%20Naseema%20Khatoon%20who%20is%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%20and%20a%20part%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20(NHRC)%20advisory%20group%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-500x500.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-150x150.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-768x768.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-600x600.jpg%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-400x400.jpg%20400w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-200x200.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-96x96.jpg%2096w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818.jpg%20773w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386775%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENaseema%20is%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%20and%20a%20part%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20(NHRC)%20advisory%20group%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constant%20fear%20of%20the%20police%2C%20the%20forced%20hiding%2C%20and%20the%20need%20to%20constantly%20run%20were%20not%20just%20external%20pressures%3B%20they%20profoundly%20shaped%20her%20self-perception%20and%20her%20struggle%20to%20define%20her%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20hard%20to%20define%20yourself%20as%20a%20daughter%20of%20a%20red-light%20area%20and%20not%20a%20sex%20worker.%20This%20is%20a%20concept%20that%20is%20unheard%20of%20to%20the%20outside%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20But%20Naseema%20never%20let%20go%20of%20her%20desire%20to%20define%20herself%20beyond%20what%20the%20world%20forced%20on%20her.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJust%20as%20someone%20who%20has%20a%20small%20vegetable%20stall%20that%20he%20pushes%20around%20on%20the%20road%2C%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20want%20their%20child%20to%20continue%20doing%20the%20same%20work%20they%20do%2C%20a%20sex%20worker%20also%20does%20not%20want%20their%20child%20to%20continue%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20She%20wants%20better%20for%20her%20kids%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naseema%20reflects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98I%20was%20always%20so%20scared%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201995%2C%20when%20Naseema%20was%20a%20young%20teen%2C%20IAS%20Rajbala%20Verma%2C%20who%20was%20posted%20as%20a%20district%20magistrate%2C%20started%20some%20programmes%20to%20help%20sex%20workers%20in%20the%20area%20learn%20skills%2C%20such%20as%20embroidery%2C%20and%20get%20access%20to%20healthcare.%20Naseema%20took%20part%20in%20one%20such%20programme%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%98Better%20Life%20Option%E2%80%99.%20She%20had%20already%20learnt%20embroidery%20from%20her%20mother%2C%20was%20skilled%20at%20it%2C%20and%20stood%20out.%20But%20even%20then%2C%20she%20struggled%20with%20the%20anxiety%20of%20having%20to%20answer%20certain%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20always%20so%20scared%20that%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20even%20speak.%20Because%20what%20if%20that%20conversation%20leads%20to%20them%20asking%20me%20where%20I%E2%80%99m%20from%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20admits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20just%2013%20years%20old%2C%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20leave%20school%20and%20move%20to%20Sitamarhi%20to%20live%20with%20her%20maternal%20grandmother.%20However%2C%20by%20this%20time%2C%20she%20had%20already%20resolved%20to%20build%20a%20life%20for%20herself%2C%20one%20that%20would%20need%20no%20hiding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20heard%20about%20an%20organisation%20there%20that%20was%20helping%20adolescent%20girls.%20I%20did%20not%20know%20what%20they%20did%20or%20how%20they%20could%20help.%20I%20was%20sure%20that%20if%20I%20just%20tried%20a%20little%2C%20I%20could%20figure%20my%20life%20out%20and%20make%20something%20of%20myself.%20So%2C%20I%20locked%20myself%20in%20a%20room%20for%20days%2C%20refused%20to%20eat%20or%20speak%20to%20anybody%2C%20until%20I%20was%20taken%20to%20where%20that%20organisation%20was%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20kept%20asking%20why%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20there%2C%20and%20I%20would%20say%20that%20there%20is%20a%20friend%20that%20I%20really%20want%20to%20meet%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20chuckles.%20Her%20persistence%20paid%20off%2C%20and%20one%20day%20she%20met%20with%20the%20people%20from%20%E2%80%98Adithi%E2%80%99%2C%20an%20organisation%20that%20works%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F255139%2Fmumbai-designer-covid19-underprivileged-women-earn-money-donation-livelihood-fashion-cloth-bags-scrunchies-gurmeen-shrivastav-srujna-ngo-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderprivileged%20women%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20next%20day%2C%20Adithi%20workers%20came%20to%20her%20house%20and%20urged%20her%20father%20to%20let%20her%20become%20a%20part%20of%20the%20organisation%20where%20she%20would%20learn%20valuable%20skills%20and%20turn%20her%20life%20around.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20so%20stunned%20when%20they%20came%20to%20our%20house.%20It%20was%20like%20my%20legs%20had%20become%20jelly%20and%20the%20cola%20that%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20serve%20them%2C%20wound%20up%20on%20their%20clothes.%20I%20laugh%20as%20I%20say%20that%20now%2C%20but%20that%20day%20I%20could%20have%20died%20of%20relief%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20worked%20with%20the%20organisation%20till%202002%2C%20becoming%20a%20skilled%20micro-level%20planner%20and%20trainer.%20Her%20years%20in%20Sitamarhi%20with%20Adithi%20taught%20her%20about%20the%20law%2C%20child%20rights%2C%20and%20the%20safety%20the%20Constitution%20grants%20each%20and%20every%20citizen%20of%20this%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Jugnu%E2%80%99%3A%20Where%20children%20express%20their%20dreams%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Naseema%20came%20back%20to%20Muzaffarpur%20in%202002%2C%20she%20saw%20the%20issues%20plaguing%20her%20home%20town%20with%20a%20renewed%20sense%20of%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20a%20raid%20in%20the%20area%20right%20next%20to%20us%2C%20women%20were%20arrested%20and%20taken%20away%20without%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20female%20constable%20because%20those%20rules%2C%20for%20some%20reason%2C%20do%20not%20apply%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20next%20day%2C%20I%20sat%20at%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20tea%20stall%2C%20watching%20as%20the%20police%20rounded%20up%20people%20from%20the%20area.%20A%20meeting%20was%20taking%20place%2C%20led%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98Samaj%20Sudhar%20Committee%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20they%20told%20the%20women%20they%20could%20learn%20skills%20like%20tailoring%2C%20embroidery%2C%20and%20other%20jobs%20offered%20by%20government%20schemes.%20When%20the%20women%20asked%20when%20they%20could%20start%20working%20and%20how%20soon%20they%20would%20get%20the%20money%2C%20they%20were%20told%20it%20would%20take%20six%20months%20to%20set%20up%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20asked%20how%20they%20could%20earn%20a%20living%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20committee%20took%20it%20as%20an%20insult.%20As%20if%20we%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20ask%20questions%20that%20dictate%20whether%20we%20get%20to%20eat%20two%20meals%20a%20day%20or%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ENaseema%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20the%20children%20in%20the%20community.%20When%20the%20woman%2C%20often%20the%20primary%20breadwinner%2C%20is%20arrested%2C%20who%20takes%20care%20of%20the%20family%3F%20The%20dependents%2C%20especially%20the%20children%2C%20are%20left%20to%20suffer.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20young%20girl%20in%20the%20household%2C%20what%20options%20does%20she%20have%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20asks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%E2%80%99s%20work%20with%20Adithi%2C%20along%20with%20her%20increasing%20involvement%20in%20community%20issues%2C%20led%20her%20to%20start%20a%20community-based%20organisation%20called%20%E2%80%98Parcham%E2%80%99%2C%20meaning%20%E2%80%98flag%E2%80%99%20in%20Hindi.%20Parcham%20was%20not%20an%20NGO%3B%20it%20was%20a%20grassroots%20organisation%20built%20by%20the%20people%20of%20the%20community%2C%20for%20the%20people%20of%20the%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu-1733397844.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jugu%20magazine%20cover%20art%2C%20written%20and%20designed%20by%20hand%20with%20elements%20such%20as%20drums%2C%20camels%2C%20a%20veil%20clad%20woman%2C%20and%20musical%20instruments.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu-1733397844.jpg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu-1733397844-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu-1733397844-500x282.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu-1733397844-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu-1733397844-1536x865.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu-1733397844-1200x676.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu-1733397844-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386776%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22901%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDesigned%20by%20hand%2C%20Jugnu%20magazine%E2%80%99s%20cover%20woman%20is%20adorned%20in%20elements%20from%20around%20the%20country%2C%20like%20Rajasthani%20bangles%20and%20a%20local%20veil%20from%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20looked%20around%20and%20saw%20what%20the%20situation%20was%20in%20terms%20of%20education%2C%20child%20rights%2C%20employment%2C%20and%20was%20trying%20to%20look%20at%20alternatives%2C%20of%20which%20there%20were%20none%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20when%20I%20interacted%20with%20the%20media%20to%20speak%20about%20these%20issues%2C%20they%20would%20somehow%20not%20mention%20that%20these%20are%20the%20children%20of%20sex%20workers%2C%20not%20sex%20workers%20themselves%2C%20just%20to%20sensationalise%20the%20reports%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20with%20Adithi%2C%20Naseema%20had%20helped%20start%20a%20magazine%20named%20%3Cem%3EInjoriya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20meaning%20%E2%80%98a%20night%20full%20of%20light%E2%80%99%2C%20inspired%20by%20the%20adult%20education%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98prod%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3Eprogrammes%20run%20by%20the%20Government%20in%20the%201970s.%20These%20programmes%20helped%20older%20women%20learn%20to%20read%20and%20write%2C%20and%20the%20material%20they%20created%20was%20collected%20and%20turned%20into%20a%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20thought%2C%20why%20not%20bring%20the%20same%20idea%20to%20my%20community%3F%20A%20magazine%20made%20by%20the%20people%20of%20the%20community%2C%20telling%20our%20own%20stories%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20decided%20that%20if%20no%20one%20else%20would%20write%20the%20truth%20about%20us%2C%20we%20would.%20Even%20though%20many%20in%20our%20community%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20read%20or%20write%2C%20we%20thought%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20matter%20if%20our%20writing%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20perfect%20%E2%80%94%20we%20would%20still%20write%20and%20share%20our%20voices%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202004%2C%20she%20started%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(meaning%20%E2%80%98firefly%E2%80%99)%2C%20a%20publication%20designed%20to%20amplify%20the%20voices%20of%20the%20marginalised.%20The%20first%20edition%2C%20a%20modest%20four-page%20photocopied%20issue%2C%20was%20printed%20with%20the%20help%20of%20local%20funds.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20a%2036-page-long%20magazine%2C%20with%2010%20active%20reporters%20from%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Mumbai%20and%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-500x654.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20poem%20from%20Jugnu%20magazine%20about%20the%20feeling%20of%20helplessness%20among%20children%20of%20sex%20workers%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-500x654.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-229x300.jpg%20229w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-768x1004.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-150x196.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045.jpg%20985w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386798%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22654%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20somebody%20asks%20them%20who%20they%20are%2C%20and%20where%20they%20come%20from%2C%20they%20can%20just%20say%20that%20they%20are%20a%20Jugnu%20reporter%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Naseema%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20a%20rule%20here%20in%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20everybody%20who%20is%20associated%20with%20us%20carries%20around%20a%20copy%20with%20them.%20If%20somebody%20asks%20them%20who%20they%20are%2C%20and%20where%20they%20come%20from%2C%20they%20can%20just%20say%20that%20they%20are%20a%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reporter%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naseema%20proudly%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20soon%20became%20more%20than%20just%20a%20magazine%3B%20it%20became%20a%20platform%20for%20children%20to%20express%20their%20dreams%2C%20hopes%2C%20and%20struggles.%20One%20of%20the%20key%20columns%20in%20the%20first%20edition%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20is%20our%20dream%3F%E2%80%9D%3B%20a%20question%20rarely%20asked%20of%20children%20from%20such%20communities.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20asked%20that%20question%2C%20and%20the%20kids%20would%20come%20and%20write%20what%20they%20wanted%20to%20become%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBecoming%20a%20voice%20for%20marginalised%20communities%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EM%20D%20Arif%2C%20a%2024-year-old%20who%20used%20to%20draw%20and%20paint%20for%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20when%20he%20was%20seven%2C%20wrote%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20become%20a%20police%20officer.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20first%20few%20editions%2C%20I%20would%20often%20draw.%20Once%2C%20I%20wrote%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98What%20is%20our%20dream%E2%80%99%20column.%20But%20now%2C%20I%20write%20about%20more%20complex%20things%20that%20we%20see%20around%20here%20in%20Muzaffarpur%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CThat%20includes%20child%20labour%20and%20identity%20politics.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20especially%20poignant%20piece%20he%20worked%20on%20covers%20the%20lives%20of%20sex%20workers%20who%20have%20given%20up%20their%20profession%20due%20to%20old%20age.%20%E2%80%9CI%20spoke%20to%20people%20and%20found%20that%20even%20though%20it%20has%20been%20years%20since%20they%20have%20retired%2C%20they%20still%20call%20themselves%20sex%20workers.%20It%20is%20so%20deeply%20ingrained%20in%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20identity%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20really%20nothing%20wrong%20in%20that%20either%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20active%20member%20of%20Parcham%20and%20now%20a%20member%20of%20his%20college%E2%80%99s%20NSS%20team%2C%20he%20often%20conducts%20meetings%2C%20telling%20people%20about%20their%20rights%20and%20teaching%20them%20how%20to%20ask%20for%20them.%20%E2%80%9CJugnu%20gave%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20the%20freedom%20to%20speak%20about%20ourselves%2C%20who%20we%20are%2C%20and%20where%20we%20come%20from%3B%20without%20hesitation%2C%20without%20fear%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%20Naseema%20wanted%20to%20continue%20her%20work%2C%20by%202012%2C%20the%20magazine%20had%20gone%20dormant%20as%20she%20moved%20to%20Rajasthan%20and%20started%20a%20family.%20But%20the%20dream%20never%20died.%20In%202021%2C%20she%20revived%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20a%20renewed%20focus%20on%20expanding%20the%20magazine%E2%80%99s%20reach%20beyond%20Muzaffarpur.%20Now%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20not%20just%20a%20magazine%20of%20the%20red-light%20district%20%E2%80%94%20it%20represented%20marginalised%20communities%20across%20Mumbai%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNot%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20know%20me%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20but%20people%20do%20know%20Prem%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Naseema%2C%20looking%20back%20at%20the%20remarkable%20journey%20of%20Premnath%2C%20a%2020-year-old%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F237538%2Frajasthan-woman-sapera-kalbelia-dance-gulabo-sapera-inspiring-padma-shree-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKalbeliya%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Barmer%2C%20Rajasthan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrem%20met%20Naseema%20in%202018%20at%20an%20event%20and%20soon%20became%20involved%20with%20Jugnu%2C%20writing%20about%20the%20nomadic%20tribes%20of%20Rajasthan.%20Growing%20up%2C%20as%20he%20saw%20his%20parents%20having%20to%20beg%20to%20bring%20food%20to%20the%20table%2C%20he%20knew%20that%20he%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20continue%20his%20education%20much%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20people%20were%20nomads.%20We%20never%20settled%20and%20as%20a%20result%20of%20that%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20land%20to%20call%20our%20own.%20Without%20an%20address%20and%20IDs%2C%20we%20cannot%20get%20proper%20documentation.%20If%20someone%20from%20our%20community%20passes%20on%2C%20there%20are%20chances%20that%20we%20might%20have%20to%20try%20a%20few%20villages%20to%20check%20if%20somebody%20would%20house%20our%20dead%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20And%20these%20are%20the%20things%20he%20writes%20about%20in%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20managed%20to%20get%20a%20college%20education%20because%20of%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%20A%20final-year%20political%20science%20major%2C%20he%20has%20become%20an%20active%20writer%20and%20reporter%2C%20shedding%20light%20on%20the%20issues%20his%20people%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEmpowering%20children%20through%20%E2%80%98Police%20Paathshaala%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%20fondly%20recalls%20the%20time%20she%20encouraged%20Prem%20to%20visit%20the%20collector%E2%80%99s%20office%20and%20present%20him%20with%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20magazine.%20Though%20hesitant%20at%20first%2C%20Prem%20took%20the%20initiative%20and%20impressed%20the%20collector%20with%20his%20determination.%20When%20Prem%20mentioned%20the%20challenges%20of%20studying%20at%20the%20%3Cem%3EGaushala%3C%2Fem%3E%20(cow-shed)%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20electricity%20at%20home%2C%20the%20collector%20immediately%20took%20steps%20to%20rectify%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20where%20we%20realised%20how%20this%20magazine%20can%20help%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Naseema.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20about%20me.%20It%E2%80%99s%20about%20any%20marginalised%20community%20that%20feels%20unheard.%E2%80%9D%20Reporters%20treat%20the%20magazine%20as%20their%20own%20constitution%2C%20and%20Naseema%20encourages%20them%20to%20share%20it%20with%20others.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20people%20pay%20you%20the%20support%20funds%2C%20great.%20If%20not%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20never%20a%20waste.%20It%20will%20at%20least%20make%20them%20realise%20that%20you%20are%20a%20reporter%20or%20writer%2C%20someone%20powerful.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202023%2C%20Naseema%20also%20started%20a%20pioneering%20initiative%2C%20called%20Police%20Paathshaala%2C%20in%20her%20hometown.%20The%20programme%20aims%20to%20change%20the%20way%20children%20of%20Chaturbhuj%20Sthan%20engage%20with%20the%20police.%20Officers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F330978%2Fkamlesh-atwal-started-nanakmatta-public-school-uttarakhand-holistic-education-for-students%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteach%20the%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20play%20with%20them%2C%20and%20even%20bring%20them%20cakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%20reflects%20on%20the%20stark%20contrast%20between%20her%20childhood%20and%20what%20these%20children%20experience%20today.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20was%20little%2C%20I%20was%20always%20told%20to%20hide%20from%20the%20police%2C%20to%20fear%20them.%20But%20these%20kids%3F%20You%20should%20see%20them%20jump%20around%20and%20boss%20the%20officers%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20quite%20funny!%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201040px)%20100vw%2C%201040px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221040%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Local%20police%20officers%20engage%20with%20children%20in%20a%20friendly%20and%20open%20environment.%20The%20scene%20conveys%20a%20sense%20of%20trust%20and%20comfort%2C%20with%20the%20children%20feeling%20at%20ease%2C%20building%20positive%20relationships%20with%20the%20officers.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861.jpg%201040w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861-300x135.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861-500x225.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861-768x346.jp